<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (2) ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas the technical requirements which motor vehicles must satisfy pursuant to national laws relate, inter alia to their liquid fuel tanks and rear protective devices; </inglise>
<eesti> tehnilised n&otilde;uded, millele mootors&otilde;idukid peavad siseriiklike &otilde;igusaktide kohaselt vastama, kehtivad muu hulgas ka mootors&otilde;idukite vedelk&uuml;tusepaakide ja tagumiste allas&otilde;idut&otilde;kete kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas those requirements differ from one Member State to another; whereas it is therefore necessary that all Member States adopt the same requirements either in addition to or in place of their existing rules, in order, in particular, to allow the EEC type approval procedure which was the subject of the Council Directive (3) of 6 February 1970 on the approximation of the laws of the Member States relating to the type approval of motor vehicles and their trailers to be applied in respect of each type of vehicle; </inglise>
<eesti> k&otilde;nealused n&otilde;uded on liikmesriigiti erinevad; seet&otilde;ttu on vajalik, et k&otilde;ik liikmesriigid kohaldaksid samu n&otilde;udeid, t&auml;iendades olemasolevaid eeskirju v&otilde;i asendades need uutega selleks, et eelk&otilde;ige oleks v&otilde;imalik rakendada iga s&otilde;idukit&uuml;&uuml;bi puhul EM&Uuml; t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitusmenetlust, mida k&auml;sitletakse n&otilde;ukogu 6. veebruari 1970. aasta direktiivis mootors&otilde;idukite ja nende haagiste t&uuml;&uuml;bikinnitust k&auml;sitlevate liikmesriikide &otilde;igusaktide &uuml;htlustamise kohta, (1) </eesti>
